# Git commit workflow (agent)

When user asks to **create a commit** or **commit and push**: format → commit → review.

## Git safety

- NEVER update git config
- NEVER destructive git (force push, hard reset) unless user explicitly requests
- NEVER skip hooks unless user explicitly requests
- NEVER force push to main/master
- Avoid `git commit --amend` unless user requested, HEAD is yours and unpushed, hook did not reject
- If commit FAILED or hook rejected → **new** commit, do not amend
- NEVER commit unless user asked; do not push unless user asked
- No interactive git (`-i`)

## Workflow

1. `git status`, `git diff`, `git log -3 --oneline`
2. Draft commit message (why, not just what)
3. Format changed `.cs` per `pre-commit-csharpier-format.mdc`
4. `git add` → `git commit`
5. Post-commit review per `post-commit-csharp-code-review.mdc`
6. Fix Blockers in follow-up commit unless user approves shipping with them noted
7. Push only when user asked

## Sync commits

Prefer message shape: `sync: mirror Core from griddungeon-game @ <short-sha>`
